@startuml
title USF Math Contracts - Global/Local Interoperation
left to right direction

rectangle "Global USF Math Domain\n(scale-aware coordinates + ids + cross-scale transforms)" as Global
rectangle "Local Runtime Math Domain\n(f32/f64/i32/i64-friendly capability internals)" as Local
rectangle "Scale Boundary Adapter\n(normalize/de-normalize + explicit conversion contracts)" as Adapter
rectangle "Capability Channels\n(physics/render/audio/pathfinding/...)" as Channels
rectangle "USF Runtime Contracts\n(metrics + realizers + phenomena + models)" as Contracts

Contracts -[#1E88E5]-> Global : declares canonical state/logic space in scale-aware terms
Global -[#FB8C00]-> Adapter : converts global values via explicit boundary operations
Adapter -[#43A047]-> Local : projects bounded local values for efficient runtime execution
Local -[#43A047]-> Channels : computes capability effects with local numeric kernels
Channels -[#43A047]-> Adapter : returns outputs requiring canonical reconciliation through adapter
Adapter -[#8E24AA]-> Global : folds local outputs back into scale-aware canonical representations
Global -[#8E24AA]-> Contracts : supplies canonical values to script/runtime contracts

note right of Adapter
Core policy:
- make expensive global math explicit
- keep local math fast where possible
- never hide cross-scale conversion boundaries
end note

note bottom
Directionally locked:
- 71 scales are core spine.
- Cross-scale operations require scale-aware math paths.
- Inside a scale, local math is preferred when bounded and valid.
end note
@enduml
